  "response": "In the history of the modern Olympics, there have been more silver medals awarded than gold medals. This is primarily due to the fact that for each event, a gold, a silver, and a bronze medal are awarded, except in cases of ties. However, there are some events, particularly in team sports or when there is a tie for a position, where multiple silver or bronze medals can be awarded, but only one gold medal is given per event. Over the years, this has resulted in a higher total number of silver medals compared to gold medals.",
